tip.text: We had the salt and pepper squid, rice paper roll duck, banana blossom, pork fried rice and pork belly (which is divine). Super friendly and helpful staff with a separate vegan and gluten free menu.
We had the bento box for brunch. Everything was delicious, except the chicken and rice. Ambience is trendy (a bit much) but reminds me of sushi samba in NYC when it first opened in the early 2000.
We had the chili squid, dumplings, superfood salad and burger. Everything is delicious and the restaurant such a gem in the London Bridge area which reminds me of the meat packing district in NYC.
The ambience was circa Ian Schrager 1990s Miami decked out in dark colors instead of white. Food was excellent. We had the Tom Yum soup, black noodles with eel and the red duck curry.
I had the duck burger. It is pulled duck in a plum sauce with cucumber and an egg. It was delicious!
My favorite is the crab and cream cheese. The multiple cheese with the pesto is really good too.

contact.facebookName: Лепим и Варим - Пельменный бутик в Столешниковом

tip.text: We were here for brunch, relaxed and yet so hipster. Fresh food, smoothies and juices. I had the egg white omelette with prawns. My friend had the smoked salmon with eggs which he inhaled.

The massages are divine. The location tucked away from the main crazy street. The therapist was extremely good, I was fading in and out during the massage. Staff professional. Will definitely go back.
We had the grilled duck which was the speciality of the restaurant. It was seasoned well and grilled to perfection. The restaurant overlooks the jungle and hidden from the main road.
Hit or miss customer service, but nice products and nice food. Spectacular scenery.
I had the Moreton bay bugs and king prawns special which comes with rice and salad. Beautifully seasoned from the rice to the seafood. It was rustic food but absolutely delicious.
The salt and pepper squid is amazing as is the pumpkin broccolini side dish. The pumpkin is like a candy party in your mouth. Service is excellent!
Definitely go for the dumplings which is mo mo, which is delicious. I got the spicy and mild. Spicy sauce is really spicy. The chicken mo mo is delicious!
Delicious Vietnamese food. Definitely go to the roof top for dinner as there are beautiful plants to add to the ambience.
Stunning hotel, one of my favorites. The pool is great. Saigon kitchen has a fantastic breakfast. The bar is beautiful and one of the hip places in HCMC.

contact.facebookName: Hotel des Arts Saigon, MGallery Collection

tip.text: Consistently delicious, great service. Trio tartare is great, warm great bread. Ambience is charming and inviting.

Future World: where art meets science; and Big Bang Data. If you are a science geek, Big Bang Data: the evolution of storage, usage and analyses. Art meets Science: unlimited imagination for everyone!
Beautiful hotel, cosy and stylish. We went there for dinner which was ok, touted one of Sri Lankan culinary delights but we unfortunately weren't too impressed. Super friendly staff.
The hotel can arrange your stay throughout Sri Lanka. Staff is wonderful and helpful and completely honest. Beautiful colonial hotel.
Not the best Italian around, a bit touristy but they do try to make you as comfortable as possible. Decent Italian.

We got the fish tasting menu. The bread was delectable, fish melts in your mouth but my favorite was the pasta with cooked in lobster broth. Divine. Definite must, plenty of waiters to fuss about you.
They are good for their seafood!
The pastas are homemade and delicious. So is the porcini, celery and truffle antipasti, one of their specialty.
The steak!
You must have the tuna and the whole wheat pasta with red pepper cream sauce. To die for!
Stunning views of the beach. Extremely enjoyable. The service is impeccable, food just ok, mostly local guests which we loved. Stop with last century's cover band music already, night entertainment!
Eclectic art everywhere
